description:
Roles & Responsibilities
Roles & Responsibilities

Handling of all ship operations including resolving operational issues with relevant parties;
To assist the chartering and operation managers as required;
Coordinating with PNI club on settlement of outstanding disputes for various voyages;
Coordinating with accounts and operations departments on payments, BL collection, and following up of outstanding accounts with relevant parties;
Handling of voyage accounts for the ships including laytime calculation and settlement of final voyage costs with ship owner and voyage charterer;
Coordinating with bunker supplier on bunkering of tugs;
Updating of data in shipment software and Google Sheets;
To control voyage expenses, optimize voyage turn around time and maximizing profitability for the respective voyages;
Site survey and attendance;
Any other duties as assigned by the company or department;
Possession of personal transportation is a plus:

Qualifications & Requirements

Professional Certificate / NITEC, ITE, Diploma or relevant drafting experience; Minimum Diploma qualification in Maritime Studies/ Logistics & Supply Chain/ related field of studies
Minimum 2 year working experience is preferred

Roles & Responsibilities
Assist operation manager to oversee and ensure smooth operations of the Company in the following areas:
· Lead the Company’s Operations staff in accordance with the Company’s visions and values;
· Improve existing operational and safety systems, processes and policies to enhance the Company’s business process and organizational planning;
· Play a significant role in developing the Company’s long-term plans, specifically in terms of, but not limited to, operational and safety excellence;
· Ensure Company’s Operational and Safety Processes is consistent or above industry standards;
· Harness opportunities to control assets, optimize costs and enhancing profitability;
· Regular meetings with Director on Operations planning;
· Enhance existing Quality Management System and ensure that the Quality Management System required are established, implemented and maintained in accordance to the Standard;
· Monitor and report on the Quality Management System’s performance to top management for review;
· Ensure Company policies are adhered to while promoting positive workplace relationships and healthy teamwork at the workplace;
· Effectively manpower planning to ensure timely order performance;
· Maintain premises and equipment licensing validity to ensure operations activities remain compliant with authority’s requirement.
